ing a ring 3 user process from executing these instructions...<br /><br />Well, it could be that Virtual PC raises a #UD exception in the virtual <br />machine. In user space, that would just cause the kernel to kill the poor <br />innocent victim. But when the kernel gets a #UD exception on what it <br />expects to be a nop, it just won't work.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
